type: web_research
title: LLM Model Routing & Auto-Switching Systems - Comprehensive Research
key_insights[16]: "LiteLLM: Most popular OSS LLM gateway, 100+ models, YAML config, fallback chains, cost tracking, budget limits","Portkey AI: Commercial gateway with semantic caching, automatic retries, load balancing, 200+ LLMs, 50+ guardrails","Not Diamond: Predictive model router, trains custom routing on eval data, up to 25% accuracy improvement, 10x cost reduction","Martian: Patent-pending model mapping tech based on mechanistic interpretability, 98% cost savings claimed, used by 300+ companies","RouteLLM (UC Berkeley): Open-source, 4 router types (SW/MF/BERT/CausalLLM), 85% cost reduction on MT Bench maintaining 95% GPT-4 quality","Semantic Router (Aurelio Labs): Embedding-based routing using ModernBERT, routes simple->fast path, complex->CoT reasoning","vLLM Semantic Router: Production-ready v0.1 Iris (Jan 2026), Rust engine, Kubernetes native","Claude Code Router (musistudio): Task-based routing (default/background/think/longContext/webSearch), supports OpenRouter/DeepSeek/Ollama/Gemini","Claude Code + OpenRouter: Set ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL, ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY='' - only Anthropic 1P provider guaranteed","LLM Cascade Pattern: Try cheap model first, escalate based on confidence/consistency/verifier - 40-60% cost savings","GPTCache: Semantic cache for LLMs, 61-68% hit rate, 97%+ accuracy, 2-10x speed improvement","Opus 4.6 pricing: $5/$25 per M tokens (same as Opus 4.5), legacy Opus 4 was $15/$75","Haiku 4.5: $1/$5, Sonnet 4.5: $3/$15, Opus 4.5/4.6: $5/$25 per M tokens","Heavy Claude Code user: $200-400/month API vs $20/month Pro plan vs $100/month Max plan","Token optimization strategies: prompt compression (50-80% reduction), caching (90% discount), RAG, CSV over JSON (40-50% savings)",Combined optimization strategies can achieve 60-80% cost reduction without quality compromise
findings[9]: LiteLLM is the de facto standard OSS gateway with best community support,claude-code-router by musistudio is purpose-built for Claude Code with task-based routing,OpenRouter integration is simplest but only guarantees Anthropic 1P provider compatibility,RouteLLM's BERT classifier is best balance of accuracy and speed for routing decisions,Cascade pattern (cheap->expensive) with confidence-based quality gates saves 40-60%,Semantic caching alone can eliminate 31% of redundant API calls,"For Claude Code specifically, the ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL env var is the key integration point",Claude Code Router supports /model command for on-the-fly model switching,Batch API offers 50% discount for non-urgent workloads ($2.50/$12.50 for Opus 4.6)
refs[9]: "https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm - LiteLLM OSS gateway","https://github.com/musistudio/claude-code-router - Claude Code Router","https://github.com/lm-sys/RouteLLM - RouteLLM framework","https://github.com/aurelio-labs/semantic-router - Semantic Router","https://portkey.ai - Portkey AI Gateway","https://www.notdiamond.ai - Not Diamond AI Router","https://route.withmartian.com - Martian Model Router","https://openrouter.ai/docs/guides/guides/claude-code-integration - OpenRouter + Claude Code","https://github.com/zilliztech/GPTCache - GPTCache semantic cache"
recommendations[7]: Use claude-code-router as primary solution for Claude Code model routing,Combine with LiteLLM for backend gateway with cost tracking and budgeting,Implement semantic cache (GPTCache or Portkey) for repeated queries,"Use Haiku 4.5 for background tasks, Sonnet 4.5 for standard coding, Opus 4.6 only for complex reasoning","Set up cascade: local model (Ollama) -> Haiku -> Sonnet -> Opus based on task complexity",Add RouteLLM-style classifier for automatic task complexity detection,Monitor costs via LiteLLM spend tracking dashboard
